buy you a drink?

08:49.112 --> 08:52.104
Oh, we can talk through
our differences while we
wait out the storm.

08:52.198 --> 08:53.233
Alvis.

08:53.324 --> 08:55.030
HECTOR: You killed two
Company men and stole papers

08:55.118 --> 08:57.780
from 1,000 Westerlyns
who are owed land on Leith.

08:57.871 --> 09:00.533
What are you going to do,
switch your genetic l.D.'s,

09:01.416 --> 09:02.701
highest bidder
takes his place?

09:03.585 --> 09:05.792
Whole families have worked
their asses off because

09:05.879 --> 09:07.335
they were promised
a better life.

09:07.422 --> 09:10.539
What kind of a man
steals from the future
of his own people?

09:10.633 --> 09:12.214
KAL: You tell me, Captain.

09:12.719 --> 09:14.880
That's a Company
execution outside.

09:15.346 --> 09:18.679
You're a Westerlyn
with boots on your own kind.

09:18.975 --> 09:20.055
Open the bag.

09:22.979 --> 09:24.594
(GUNS COCKING)

09:26.983 --> 09:28.769
Oh, shit.

09:31.071 --> 09:32.527
You're all alone, son.

09:37.911 --> 09:38.946
Get back.

09:39.829 --> 09:40.864
Shit.

09:41.331 --> 09:42.696
(GRUNTING)

09:47.420 --> 09:48.455
Hey!

09:52.342 --> 09:53.673
You next?

09:57.055 --> 09:58.090
HECTOR: Okay. Okay.

10:02.102 --> 10:03.182
Okay, listen up!

10:03.978 --> 10:05.263
Let's all be smart.

10:08.108 --> 10:09.473
(GROANING)

10:10.151 --> 10:12.062
Oh, damn it.

10:13.822 --> 10:14.937
Kai!

10:17.325 --> 10:19.691
You, hero!
Lock it up! Now!

10:24.582 --> 10:26.243
(SCREAMING)

10:37.720 --> 10:39.711
(ALL GROANING)

10:43.476 --> 10:45.091
SURJA: Everyone,
put them in here.

10:53.069 --> 10:54.730
I can help your friend.
I'm a doctor.

11:01.411 --> 11:03.402
We need to get him upstairs
to an operating table, now.

11:03.496 --> 11:04.576
JOHN: I'll help.

11:04.747 --> 11:06.578
Hey, hey, hey. Not you.

11:07.500 --> 11:09.832
SURJA: Now, we'll be gone
as soon as the rain stops.

11:10.795 --> 11:12.581
Until then,
I got one rule.

11:12.922 --> 11:14.423
Don't be stupid,
don't die.

11:15.133 --> 11:17.670
Bad luck pulling ajob
right before the rain, huh?

11:18.428 --> 11:21.010
You trying to be funny?
No, sir. No, no.

11:22.432 --> 11:25.048
Look, you stole a whack
of land l.D. claims,
we heard.

11:25.143 --> 11:26.258
And...

11:27.353 --> 11:28.968
You got a way
to move them?
Yeah, why?

11:29.772 --> 11:31.558
Well, speaking for
all the other drunks
in here,

11:31.649 --> 11:33.981
we all just want you
happy and gone.

11:34.819 --> 11:37.481
We got a fence lined up.
It's off-world somewhere,
okay?

11:39.282 --> 11:40.317
Somewhere, huh?

11:40.533 --> 11:43.275
Your friend up there, he,
uh, put this job together,
huh?

11:45.788 --> 11:47.449
See,|usedto
beinthelWe.
